#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter describes the usage of the <command>transactional-update</command> command."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:20
#, no-c-format
msgid "2023-11-03"
msgstr "2023-11-03"

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "In case you do not reboot your machine before performing further changes, the <command>transactional-update</command> command will create a new snapshot from the current root file system. This means that you will end up with several parallel snapshots, each including that particular change but not changes from the other invocations of the command. After reboot, the most recently created snapshot will be used as your new root file system, and it will not include changes done in the previous snapshots."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>transactional-update</command> usage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>transactional-update</command> command enables the atomic installation or removal of updates; updates are applied only if all of them can be successfully installed. <command>transactional-update</command> creates a snapshot of your system and uses it to update the system. Later you can restore this snapshot. All changes become active only after reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <command>transactional-update</command> command syntax is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: slemicro_transactional_updates.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"transactional-update <option>[option]</option> <replaceable>[general_command]</replaceable> <replaceable>[package_command]</replaceable> <replaceable>standalone_command</replaceable>\n"
msgstr ""

